    • m

      public double[] m
      using the region moments and area, calculates parameters needed for a bounding ellipse. The equation for rotation of an ellipse by angle alpha: x(t) = xCenter + aParam*cos(alpha)*cos(t) − bParam*sin(alpha)*sin(t) y(t) = yCenter + aParam*sin(alpha)*cos(t) + bParam*cos(alpha)*sin(t) returns v0x = aParam * cos(alpha); v1x = bParam * sin(alpha); v0y = aParam * sin(alpha); v1y = bParam * cos(alpha); e0 = first eigenvalue e1 = 2nd eigenvalue m is []{v0x, v1x, v0y, v1y}
